   <title>1.&nbsp;Hardware Requirements</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="html.css" type="text/css"><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.68.1"><link rel="start" href="index.html" title="LIMS Help Pages"><link rel="up" href="ch24.html" title="Chapter&nbsp;24.&nbsp;System Requirements"><link rel="prev" href="ch24.html" title="Chapter&nbsp;24.&nbsp;System Requirements"><link rel="next" href="ch24s02.html" title="2.&nbsp;Software Requirements"></head><body bgcolor="white" text="black" link="#0000FF" vlink="#840084" alink="#0000FF"><div class="navheader"><table width="100%" summary="Navigation header"><tr><th colspan="3" align="center">1.&nbsp;Hardware Requirements</th></tr><tr><td width="20%" align="left"><a accesskey="p" href="ch24.html">Prev</a>&nbsp;</td><th width="60%" align="center">Chapter&nbsp;24.&nbsp;System Requirements</th><td width="20%" align="right">&nbsp;<a accesskey="n" href="ch24s02.html">Next</a></td></tr></table><hr></div><div class="section" lang="en"><div class="titlepage"><div><div><h2 class="title" style="clear: both"><a name="d0e17093"></a>1.&nbsp;Hardware Requirements</h2></div></div></div><p>The following hardware is recommended for running the alDente LIMS:</p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>CPU :</p></li><li><p>RAM :</p></li><li><p>Static disk storage space :</p></li></ul></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="opencircle"><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>System Installation -</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Web Server:</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Core Laboratory Data -</p></li></ul></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="opencircle"><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Projects directory: 20k / read</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Archive: 300k / read</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Database: 4K / read</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Backups:</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Cache:</p></li></ul></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>Barcode Printer and Labels (sticky 1000 recommended for low temperature applications -&gt; -80 degrees)</p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="opencircle"><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p><span class="emphasis"><em>Zebra Z4Mplus (300dpi) - recommended for large label printing</em></span></p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p><span class="emphasis"><em>Zebra 105SL (300dpi) - recommended for thin label printing (below .6")</em></span></p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Zebra 110XiIII (300dpi) - thin label printer with more features than the 105SL</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Zebra S600 (200dpi)</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Brady MVP (300dpi)</p></li></ul></div></li></ul></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>Wireless Barcode Scanners - not mandatory, but recommended for effective lab tracking. </p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="opencircle"><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p><span class="emphasis"><em>HP hx2750 (PocketPC SYS-H-FA301) and Socket Hand Scan Card (1D POS-SCN-S-5006) combination - recommended</em></span></p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Compaq 3850 IPAQ (1D scanner) - discontinued</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>CodeCorp CodeReader2.0 (1D/2D scanner) - for connecting to a desktop (portable scanner only)</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Symbol PPT2800 PocketPC (1D scanner)</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>Symbol PDT8100 PocketPC (1D/2D scanner)</p></li></ul></div></li><li><p>Wireless Hubs (at least 2 are recommended to provide redundancy)</p></li></ul></div><div class="sidebar"><div class="itemizedlist"><h3><a name="d0e17182"></a>Change log:</h3><ul type="opencircle"><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2000: Symbol.</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2002: changed to Compaq 3850 for standard scanner of choice (in colour, faster response)</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2003: Compaq 3850 discontinued</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2003: Symbol PPT2800 (PPT2846-TRBZ0YUS) adopted as 1D scanner of choice (now in colour and faster; also more sturdy than compaq). Also, Compaq 3850s are unavailable.</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2004: Symbol PDT8100 (PDT8146) adopted as 2D scanner of choice. However, it would be beneficial to switch to a version w/o a keypad.</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2005: HP hx2750 Pocket PC (SYS-H-FA301) adopted as standard handheld, with a SocketScan SDIO card for scanning (POS-SCN-S-5006).</p></li><li style="list-style-type: circle"><p>2006/05/09: Thin label printers added (105SL and 110XiIII) as the S600/Z4M was not designed for labels thinner than .6"</p></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="navfooter"><hr><table width="100%" summary="Navigation footer"><tr><td width="40%" align="left"><a accesskey="p" href="ch24.html">Prev</a>&nbsp;</td><td width="20%" align="center"><a accesskey="u" href="ch24.html">Up</a></td><td width="40%" align="right">&nbsp;<a accesskey="n" href="ch24s02.html">Next</a></td></tr><tr><td width="40%" align="left" valign="top">Chapter&nbsp;24.&nbsp;System Requirements&nbsp;</td><td width="20%" align="center"><a accesskey="h" href="index.html">Home</a></td><td width="40%" align="right" valign="top">&nbsp;2.&nbsp;Software Requirements</td></tr></table></div></body></html>